This paper deals with improving the robustness of image classification systems against adversarial attacks, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves developing new network architectures and training methods, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves training neural networks, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
